description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/transport/slip_transport.c
Lines: 527-569

In slip_transport_send(), if slip_encode() fails, the mutex is properly unlocked (line 549), but the stats.tx_errors increment happens before unlock:

    ret = slip_encode(ipv6, len, ctx->tx_frame, sizeof(ctx->tx_frame), &frame_len);
    if (ret < 0) {
        ctx->stats.tx_errors++;
        k_mutex_unlock(&ctx->tx_mutex);
        return ret;
    }

This is correct, but compare with the success path error (lines 556-567):

    if (ctx->uart_dev != NULL) {
        ...
        ctx->stats.tx_packets++;
        ctx->stats.tx_bytes += (uint32_t)len;
    } else {
        ctx->stats.tx_errors++;
        k_mutex_unlock(&ctx->tx_mutex);  // Unlock here
        return -ENODEV;
    }

    k_mutex_unlock(&ctx->tx_mutex);  // And here
    return 0;

The early return at line 565-566 correctly unlocks and returns, while the normal path unlocks at line 568. This is actually correct behavior.

However, stats.tx_errors at line 564 is incremented under tx_mutex, which is inconsistent with how stats are accessed elsewhere (without synchronization). This is part of the broader stats synchronization issue but creates an inconsistency in the code.
